1
00:00:34,617 --> 00:00:37,954
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

2
00:00:38,538 --> 00:00:40,957
Mi-sook, congrats on going back to work.

3
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:42,500
Thank you.

4
00:00:42,584 --> 00:00:43,960
Good job, Bom.

5
00:00:44,044 --> 00:00:45,587
-I'll put in three candles.
-All right.

6
00:00:46,087 --> 00:00:47,464
-Wow.
-Ta-da.

7
00:00:47,547 --> 00:00:48,590
It opened.

8
00:00:54,012 --> 00:00:54,888
Hello.

9
00:00:54,971 --> 00:00:56,890
Welcome. Wait…

10
00:00:59,768 --> 00:01:01,519
Who are you people?

11
00:01:03,521 --> 00:01:04,397
I got a job.

12
00:01:05,273 --> 00:01:06,483
All thanks to you.

13
00:01:11,154 --> 00:01:12,363
Goodness me.

14
00:01:30,215 --> 00:01:32,383
What do you think you're doing?
Let go of her.

15
00:01:32,467 --> 00:01:34,010
-Damn it. Let go of me.
-Hold on.

16
00:01:34,093 --> 00:01:35,929
Keum-bo!

17
00:01:38,097 --> 00:01:39,265
What's going on here?

18
00:01:39,891 --> 00:01:42,143
-Just stop fighting it and come on.
-Let go!

19
00:01:42,227 --> 00:01:43,186
Who the hell are you?

20
00:01:43,853 --> 00:01:45,104
That's why

21
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:48,775
you should've taught your daughter better.

22
00:01:49,442 --> 00:01:50,443
Take care of them.

23
00:01:50,527 --> 00:01:53,363
Jeez. Lady, just get back inside.

24
00:01:53,446 --> 00:01:54,656
Step aside already.

25
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:03,706
-No!
-Who the hell are you?

26
00:02:04,958 --> 00:02:06,126
-Mi-sook.
-Damn it.

27
00:02:20,598 --> 00:02:21,724
Are you okay?

28
00:02:32,485 --> 00:02:34,571
Stop. That hurts.

29
00:02:35,738 --> 00:02:36,865
You.

30
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:48,918
Keum-bo! Watch out!

31
00:02:53,715 --> 00:02:55,717
Go after my daughters…

32
00:02:57,302 --> 00:02:58,845
TAEKKYEON

33
00:02:58,928 --> 00:03:00,930
…and you'll end up in hell, mister.

34
00:03:03,224 --> 00:03:04,058
Honey!

35
00:03:57,195 --> 00:03:59,364
You bastard!

36
00:03:59,447 --> 00:04:01,866
Hey! Stop that!

37
00:04:03,368 --> 00:04:04,786
Stop that!

38
00:04:08,122 --> 00:04:09,123
Let's go.

39
00:04:11,626 --> 00:04:13,628
-Dad, are you okay?
-Yeah, I'm fine. Are you?

40
00:04:13,711 --> 00:04:14,671
Yeah.

41
00:04:16,714 --> 00:04:17,632
Are you okay, honey?

42
00:04:26,391 --> 00:04:29,435
EPISODE 15: NO MERCY

43
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:33,189
I really think I might need an X-ray.

44
00:04:33,273 --> 00:04:35,483
I told you I was just there
to see my little sister.

45
00:04:35,566 --> 00:04:38,569
There he is!
Man, that scoundrel is rotten to the core.

46
00:04:38,653 --> 00:04:39,737
We're the victims here.

47
00:04:39,821 --> 00:04:41,572
-My heart is still racing!
-Stop hitting me!

48
00:04:41,656 --> 00:04:43,658
You thought you could
come after my daughter?

49
00:04:43,741 --> 00:04:45,201
You punk!

50
00:04:48,162 --> 00:04:50,248
What did your parents do
before opening the restaurant?

51
00:04:50,331 --> 00:04:52,250
Where did they first meet?

52
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:54,127
I heard they met at a gym.

53
00:04:54,711 --> 00:04:57,380
He was a Taekkyeon master,
and she was Little Miss Martial Arts.

54
00:04:58,006 --> 00:04:59,048
I see.

55
00:05:01,301 --> 00:05:04,595
When did Go Bok-cheol team up with them?

56
00:05:05,346 --> 00:05:08,558
A while ago, Ms. Song asked
if my brother had been released.

57
00:05:08,641 --> 00:05:09,726
Those good-for-nothings.

58
00:05:11,019 --> 00:05:12,603
Bom, you must've been so scared.

59
00:05:14,230 --> 00:05:17,900
I was fine because
I had Auntie Nora by my side.

60
00:05:17,984 --> 00:05:20,528
We even called the police.

61
00:05:26,284 --> 00:05:28,995
I recognized the man
who dragged Ms. Hong away earlier.

62
00:05:31,289 --> 00:05:32,123
I've seen him before.

63
00:05:32,999 --> 00:05:35,001
When? Where did you see him?

64
00:05:37,003 --> 00:05:38,046
When I was ten…

65
00:05:40,089 --> 00:05:41,132
At my house.

66
00:05:49,807 --> 00:05:50,933
Where is the kid?

67
00:05:51,017 --> 00:05:53,186
-We don't know.
-We swear we don't!

68
00:05:54,437 --> 00:05:56,022
Where the hell is she?

69
00:05:56,105 --> 00:05:58,483
-I really don't know.
-Tell me where she is!

70
00:06:02,445 --> 00:06:05,031
-<i>You'd better hide yourself well</i>
-Where could she be?

71
00:06:06,365 --> 00:06:08,451
<i>You don't want to get caught</i>

72
00:06:11,829 --> 00:06:12,955
What is all this?

73
00:06:16,334 --> 00:06:17,877
I guess she's not here.

74
00:06:19,670 --> 00:06:21,422
There's just a whole lot of wine.

75
00:06:39,315 --> 00:06:40,316
Damn it.

76
00:06:41,818 --> 00:06:43,945
Don't just stand there. Look for her.

77
00:06:44,028 --> 00:06:45,780
-Sorry, sir.
-You punk.

78
00:06:47,907 --> 00:06:51,911
Man, where the hell is that little rat?

79
00:06:55,623 --> 00:06:57,250
I don't think she's over here, sir.

80
00:06:57,333 --> 00:06:59,418
-Did you check thoroughly?
-Yes, I did.

81
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:01,170
Damn it.

82
00:07:05,133 --> 00:07:06,551
Where could she be hiding?

83
00:07:08,052 --> 00:07:10,221
-Check outside again.
-Yes, sir.

84
00:07:26,070 --> 00:07:29,699
Back then, everyone was talking
about the rich girl who was kidnapped.

85
00:07:29,782 --> 00:07:32,785
I remember moms gathering their kids
before the sun set.

86
00:07:33,578 --> 00:07:35,288
So you weren't abducted?

87
00:07:36,873 --> 00:07:39,584
The truth is, I hid in the basement

88
00:07:40,418 --> 00:07:41,335
for three whole days.

89
00:08:25,713 --> 00:08:28,174
You blew the plan
because you couldn't catch one damn kid.

90
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:32,345
Who knew that kid could run that fast?

91
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:34,347
But

92
00:08:34,430 --> 00:08:36,682
you still don't know where she is, right?

93
00:08:42,396 --> 00:08:45,316
What if she got out
and got hit by a car or something?

94
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:50,029
I checked every emergency room
in the area.

95
00:08:50,613 --> 00:08:51,447
She wasn't there.

96
00:08:55,701 --> 00:08:57,328
Continue demanding a ransom for now.

97
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:00,081
If she never returns,

98
00:09:01,499 --> 00:09:02,833
this will be the perfect crime.

99
00:09:09,298 --> 00:09:10,550
Damn it.

100
00:09:11,175 --> 00:09:12,009
A ransom?

101
00:09:13,427 --> 00:09:16,305
Are you suggesting

102
00:09:16,389 --> 00:09:19,392
that we pay off the abductors
to get the kid back?

103
00:09:20,685 --> 00:09:23,104
Do you know how much I pay in taxes?

104
00:09:23,187 --> 00:09:24,272
It's been three days.

105
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:26,482
How can the police not find
one measly kid?

106
00:09:26,566 --> 00:09:28,317
We're not suggesting you pay them off.

107
00:09:28,859 --> 00:09:30,778
-We can use it to lure them out--
-Look here.

108
00:09:30,861 --> 00:09:32,530
If we pay the ransom now,

109
00:09:33,114 --> 00:09:36,784
she'll only become a walking target
for more abductors.

110
00:09:36,867 --> 00:09:38,035
Sir.

111
00:09:38,119 --> 00:09:40,538
If we provoke the captors,

112
00:09:41,205 --> 00:09:42,915
it could put Ms. Kang in danger.

113
00:09:42,999 --> 00:09:44,292
No.

114
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:45,293
Absolutely not.

115
00:09:45,376 --> 00:09:47,962
We must bring back our Eun-joo,
even if it costs all our fortune.

116
00:09:48,045 --> 00:09:49,213
This all happened

117
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:54,427
because of you, Choi In-ja,
and that silly vanity of yours!

118
00:09:54,510 --> 00:09:55,469
What?

119
00:09:55,553 --> 00:09:57,930
You paraded that kid around everywhere

120
00:09:58,014 --> 00:10:01,559
and plastered her face
all over the magazines and TV shows!

121
00:10:01,642 --> 00:10:03,019
She wasn't kidnapped out there!

122
00:10:03,102 --> 00:10:04,770
The burglars broke into our home!

123
00:10:04,854 --> 00:10:06,480
You threw a party every damn day,

124
00:10:06,564 --> 00:10:09,483
inviting reporters, directors,
and even studio heads.

125
00:10:09,567 --> 00:10:13,529
You're the one who dragged
all those strangers into this house.

126
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:14,530
So?

127
00:10:14,614 --> 00:10:16,324
Are you just giving up on our daughter?

128
00:10:16,407 --> 00:10:18,451
We need to get Eun-joo back!

129
00:10:18,534 --> 00:10:20,620
We don't even know if she's safe,

130
00:10:20,703 --> 00:10:23,205
so why would we negotiate
with those scoundrels?

131
00:10:23,956 --> 00:10:24,874
I'd rather put

132
00:10:25,374 --> 00:10:28,252
a bounty on the criminals' heads instead.

133
00:10:29,253 --> 00:10:31,172
-Honey.
-I refuse

134
00:10:31,255 --> 00:10:34,550
to spend even a single cent on ransom!

135
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:38,554
My poor Eun-joo!

136
00:10:38,638 --> 00:10:39,805
My Eun-joo…

137
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:42,224
Detective…

138
00:10:43,684 --> 00:10:45,895
Honey, what about our Eun-joo?

139
00:10:49,565 --> 00:10:50,483
Where were you?

140
00:10:51,192 --> 00:10:52,401
In the basement.

141
00:10:54,278 --> 00:10:55,196
Wait…

142
00:10:56,947 --> 00:10:58,574
Eun-joo!

143
00:10:58,658 --> 00:10:59,492
Ms. Kang!

144
00:10:59,575 --> 00:11:01,494
-Eun-joo!
-Ms. Kang!

145
00:11:01,577 --> 00:11:02,495
Come here.

146
00:11:02,578 --> 00:11:04,455
Eun-joo!

147
00:11:05,623 --> 00:11:07,083
Where in the world were you?

148
00:11:07,166 --> 00:11:08,376
Are you hurt anywhere?

149
00:11:08,459 --> 00:11:10,670
Honey, our Eun-joo is back.

150
00:11:14,590 --> 00:11:15,508
Eun-joo…

151
00:11:22,890 --> 00:11:24,016
You must've been so scared.

152
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:25,726
You must've been scared.

153
00:11:32,066 --> 00:11:33,943
It's incredible
that you made it back alive.

154
00:11:34,026 --> 00:11:35,486
After that incident,

155
00:11:36,237 --> 00:11:38,447
my mom filed for divorce,

156
00:11:38,948 --> 00:11:41,492
and I left for the US with her.

157
00:11:42,076 --> 00:11:45,246
I stopped using the name
Kang Eun-joo after that.

158
00:11:46,664 --> 00:11:48,040
That is, until I met you all.

159
00:11:48,749 --> 00:11:50,668
And you're saying the abductor from then

160
00:11:51,419 --> 00:11:53,629
was the same man
who tried to drag me away today?

161
00:11:57,466 --> 00:11:58,592
Yes, I know those eyes.

162
00:11:59,343 --> 00:12:00,261
It was him.

163
00:12:01,971 --> 00:12:04,473
I still have nightmares
about it sometimes.

164
00:12:05,141 --> 00:12:07,935
Ms. Song was already working
for Hanmin back then, right?

165
00:12:08,602 --> 00:12:09,645
By the chairman's side?

166
00:12:11,439 --> 00:12:15,067
Song Ju-ran wasn't just occasionally
hiring a thug to intimidate people.

167
00:12:16,402 --> 00:12:17,903
They've been long-time partners.

168
00:12:28,247 --> 00:12:29,540
Are you hurt anywhere?

169
00:12:30,207 --> 00:12:31,876
I'm more worried about Nora.

170
00:12:31,959 --> 00:12:33,586
I know it must be upsetting for her,

171
00:12:33,669 --> 00:12:36,881
but that kidnapping incident is
also quite a touchy subject for my family.

172
00:12:36,964 --> 00:12:38,966
Given the history of incidents,

173
00:12:39,049 --> 00:12:42,011
we need to find out Song Ju-ran's ties
to that kidnapper first.

174
00:12:43,053 --> 00:12:44,054
But how do we find him?

175
00:12:44,638 --> 00:12:45,473
We don't even know his face.

176
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:47,933
You already do.

177
00:12:49,268 --> 00:12:50,269
Horang Auto Repair Shop.

178
00:12:51,562 --> 00:12:52,855
That scary guy from the repair shop?

179
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:55,774
Okay.

180
00:12:55,858 --> 00:12:57,485
I'll help with that since I know his face.

181
00:12:58,861 --> 00:13:00,696
I'm sure I'll find something
if I tail Ms. Song.

182
00:13:03,032 --> 00:13:05,534
It's time you went public
as the head of Yeouido Pirates, Keum-bo.

183
00:13:06,577 --> 00:13:08,370
Once we become Hanmin's public enemy,

184
00:13:08,454 --> 00:13:11,790
the attention alone will be enough
to keep Hanmin in line.

185
00:13:17,379 --> 00:13:18,422
I concur.

186
00:13:18,506 --> 00:13:21,675
Let's make Hong Keum-bo's face known
across the country.

187
00:13:29,183 --> 00:13:30,935
<i>Yeouido Pirates hereby declares its intent</i>

188
00:13:31,018 --> 00:13:34,980
<i>to formally participate in the management</i>
<i>of Hanmin Investment &amp; Securities.</i>

189
00:13:35,814 --> 00:13:38,943
In order to rein in
Chairman Kang's unilateral management,

190
00:13:39,026 --> 00:13:41,111
Hanmin's current governance structure
must be reformed.

191
00:13:41,195 --> 00:13:42,112
YEOUIDO PIRATES CEO HONG KEUM-BO'S
PRESS CONFERENCE

192
00:13:42,196 --> 00:13:45,491
Hanmin will collapse from the inside out
if we don't take action now.

193
00:13:46,075 --> 00:13:49,537
<i>Hanmin has not issued</i>
<i>an official statement on the matter.</i>

194
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:51,580
PERSONAL INFORMATION FORM
HONG KEUM-BO

195
00:13:54,542 --> 00:13:58,379
Who was the idiot division head
in charge of Hong Keum-bo?

196
00:13:58,462 --> 00:14:00,422
After Albert,

197
00:14:01,966 --> 00:14:03,551
it was Mr. Cha Jung-il.

198
00:14:05,261 --> 00:14:08,931
After the restructuring, she did oversee
some menial tasks in Research.

199
00:14:09,014 --> 00:14:11,183
She was mouthy, often defiant,

200
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:14,019
and made it obvious
that she hated delivering coffee.

201
00:14:14,103 --> 00:14:15,771
She was good at writing reports
and translating,

202
00:14:15,854 --> 00:14:17,606
it was just so annoying.

203
00:14:17,690 --> 00:14:20,484
I thought she just looked older,
but if she's actually 35…

204
00:14:20,568 --> 00:14:21,819
BIRTHDATE: DECEMBER 24, 1963

205
00:14:21,902 --> 00:14:23,279
She's 36?

206
00:14:23,362 --> 00:14:25,197
Then she was a real baby face, sir.

207
00:14:27,324 --> 00:14:29,702
She managed to trick everyone around her.

208
00:14:29,785 --> 00:14:33,080
Release all of her personal details
to the press.

209
00:14:34,206 --> 00:14:36,250
Focus on attacking her character.

210
00:14:37,751 --> 00:14:38,711
You two may leave.

211
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:47,720
The slush fund probe
could've been an excuse.

212
00:14:48,220 --> 00:14:50,472
She may have been
after the money from the start.

213
00:14:50,973 --> 00:14:52,725
I suspect that as well, sir.

214
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:06,030
Did you know?

215
00:15:06,822 --> 00:15:07,781
Know what?

216
00:15:07,865 --> 00:15:08,824
About Ms. Hong!

217
00:15:11,118 --> 00:15:12,745
Mr. Lee Yong-gi, did you know?

218
00:15:13,829 --> 00:15:15,956
Actually, don't say anything to anyone.

219
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:17,958
It'll just get you interrogated
by the chairman.

220
00:15:19,668 --> 00:15:21,837
Ms. Go wasn't at her desk today, was she?

221
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:24,298
I heard she faxed in her resignation
and suddenly quit.

222
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:25,841
I get it now.

223
00:15:26,425 --> 00:15:28,969
President Shin must've recruited her.

224
00:15:29,053 --> 00:15:31,180
He took his assistant with him.

225
00:15:31,263 --> 00:15:32,723
Wait a minute.

226
00:15:32,806 --> 00:15:36,769
What's the connection
between Hong Keum-bo and Shin Jung-woo?

227
00:15:38,395 --> 00:15:40,272
Maybe Ms. Go was the common link?

228
00:15:41,690 --> 00:15:42,608
That must be it.

229
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:44,443
That means…

230
00:15:46,111 --> 00:15:47,071
Right?

231
00:15:47,154 --> 00:15:48,864
<i>Gosh…</i>

232
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:49,907
Right?

233
00:15:54,954 --> 00:15:55,913
Sir.

234
00:15:56,455 --> 00:15:58,832
I just faxed over
Hong Keum-bo's profile to you.

235
00:15:58,916 --> 00:16:00,209
Hello, sir.

236
00:16:00,292 --> 00:16:03,087
Please make sure
the article includes those keywords.

237
00:16:04,004 --> 00:16:07,216
"Hong Keum-bo, breach of duty,
and moral hazard."

238
00:16:12,554 --> 00:16:15,099
We will certainly commit
to the advertising spend.

239
00:16:15,182 --> 00:16:16,350
You have my word.

240
00:16:16,433 --> 00:16:18,143
You have my word, sir.

241
00:16:18,644 --> 00:16:21,230
What are you doing? Seriously?

242
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:22,982
I told you to stop taking pictures.

243
00:16:23,065 --> 00:16:24,358
Damn it.

244
00:16:24,441 --> 00:16:26,151
Then let's proceed with the interview.

245
00:16:26,235 --> 00:16:28,696
-Hong Keum-bo is your daughter, correct?
-Yes.

246
00:16:28,779 --> 00:16:30,864
Did you know about her involvement
in Yeouido Pirates?

247
00:16:30,948 --> 00:16:31,782
Pirates?

248
00:16:31,865 --> 00:16:34,284
What do you know about
your daughter's suspicious activities?

249
00:16:34,368 --> 00:16:36,537
Watch what you're saying, mister.

250
00:16:36,620 --> 00:16:37,538
Enough!

251
00:16:37,621 --> 00:16:39,581
We're trying to run a business here,
so leave.

252
00:16:39,665 --> 00:16:40,749
-Go.
-Leave!

253
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,793
-Get out!
-Honey, be careful.

254
00:16:42,876 --> 00:16:43,919
Get out of here now.

255
00:16:44,003 --> 00:16:46,296
Leave! Go!

256
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:47,965
-Be careful.
-Get out.

257
00:16:48,048 --> 00:16:50,009
-Leave now!
-Go!

258
00:16:50,092 --> 00:16:51,427
ULLALA CHICKEN

259
00:16:54,638 --> 00:16:56,515
Get out of here!

260
00:16:59,268 --> 00:17:01,645
What in the world is going on?

261
00:17:03,147 --> 00:17:04,273
WHO IS THE FORMER FSS INSPECTOR
"HONG KEUM-BO"?

262
00:17:04,356 --> 00:17:07,568
FORMER FSS INSPECTOR DECLARES INTENT
TO TAKE PART IN SECURITIES FIRM MANAGEMENT

263
00:17:09,111 --> 00:17:10,154
HONG KEUM-BO, CEO

264
00:17:10,237 --> 00:17:11,405
ETHICAL CONCERNS
AND BREACH OF DUTY ALLEGATIONS

265
00:17:12,948 --> 00:17:13,866
Mr. Nam.

266
00:17:13,949 --> 00:17:16,577
Is that rumor about Ms. Hong true?

267
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:17,953
Did she leak insider information

268
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:20,414
and buy stocks with private loans
she got from Myeongdong?

269
00:17:20,497 --> 00:17:21,623
Shut it!

270
00:17:21,707 --> 00:17:22,708
How would I know?

271
00:17:22,791 --> 00:17:26,045
There was a reason she threw herself into
investigating Hanmin's slush fund.

272
00:17:26,128 --> 00:17:27,171
Exactly.

273
00:17:27,254 --> 00:17:28,881
All that moral integrity was an act.

274
00:17:28,964 --> 00:17:29,882
I knew it.

275
00:17:33,135 --> 00:17:34,011
-I knew something was fishy…
-Move.

276
00:17:43,479 --> 00:17:44,438
You knew, didn't you?

277
00:17:45,314 --> 00:17:46,648
What did I know?

278
00:17:47,941 --> 00:17:51,528
Why is everyone, from top to bottom,
ripping me a new one?

279
00:17:52,112 --> 00:17:53,447
Do I look like her spokesperson?

280
00:17:53,530 --> 00:17:56,867
Is she really planning to take a shot
at Chairman Kang Pil-beom?

281
00:17:57,451 --> 00:17:59,495
She'll just toss away
her career and future?

282
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,294
These articles are
just the tip of the iceberg.

283
00:18:07,377 --> 00:18:11,173
Rumors about her are spreading
through Yeouido, Myeongdong, and Euljiro.

284
00:18:11,256 --> 00:18:15,219
Did you, by any chance,
plant her inside Hanmin on purpose?

285
00:18:17,513 --> 00:18:18,722
Are you in on it?

286
00:18:19,890 --> 00:18:22,267
Do you take me for a thief, punk?

287
00:18:23,894 --> 00:18:24,853
Nam Dong-gi.

288
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:27,481
You keep your eyes shut
and your ears covered.

289
00:18:27,564 --> 00:18:28,565
Got that?

290
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:29,942
Damn it.

291
00:18:32,111 --> 00:18:33,403
What if we end up in the crossfire?

292
00:18:33,487 --> 00:18:35,364
Shut your mouth too! Shut it!

293
00:18:35,948 --> 00:18:38,534
-Get out!
-There's definitely something going on.

294
00:18:39,743 --> 00:18:40,828
I'm going to uncover it all.

295
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:47,584
DIRECTOR YUN JAE-BEOM

296
00:18:50,629 --> 00:18:52,548
It's less a fight for management control

297
00:18:52,631 --> 00:18:53,674
and more a war of public opinion.

298
00:18:54,258 --> 00:18:57,427
The chairman is intent on
burying Hong Keum-bo.

299
00:18:58,011 --> 00:19:00,055
All those puzzle pieces
that weirdly didn't fit

300
00:19:00,139 --> 00:19:02,432
are finally starting to fall into place.

301
00:19:04,226 --> 00:19:05,519
Ms. Hong Keum-bo.

302
00:19:05,602 --> 00:19:07,020
So that's how

303
00:19:07,604 --> 00:19:11,316
she immediately knew something was up
in the Trading Division back then.

304
00:19:12,442 --> 00:19:13,694
How is it at the office?

305
00:19:13,777 --> 00:19:16,029
From the minions to the division heads,

306
00:19:16,113 --> 00:19:18,615
the company morale is at an all-time low.

307
00:19:18,699 --> 00:19:21,160
And distrust in the management
is through the roof.

308
00:19:21,243 --> 00:19:23,871
It's because the chairman and Ms. Song

309
00:19:23,954 --> 00:19:27,291
make all the decisions themselves
in their secret meetings.

310
00:19:27,791 --> 00:19:29,918
For the company's sake,

311
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:33,213
he should sit down with Yeouido Pirates
and take them on face-to-face.

312
00:19:33,297 --> 00:19:35,132
My thoughts exactly.

313
00:19:35,215 --> 00:19:38,677
But where did Hong Keum-bo get
all that money to buy Hanmin stocks?

314
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:40,387
That's the mystery.

315
00:19:40,971 --> 00:19:44,141
Rumors say that it's
Shin Jung-woo's personal funds,

316
00:19:44,224 --> 00:19:46,560
but we're talking about
hundreds of billions of won here.

317
00:19:57,529 --> 00:19:58,363
KANG PIL-BEOM'S FAMILY TREE

318
00:19:58,447 --> 00:20:00,824
According to Mr. Cha,
Hanmin has no countermeasures prepared.

319
00:20:00,908 --> 00:20:02,159
There's no task force either.

320
00:20:02,242 --> 00:20:04,536
They're solely focused on
attacking Hong Keum-bo.

321
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:08,248
I think they ran the numbers
and decided she wasn't a threat,

322
00:20:08,332 --> 00:20:10,459
since the chairman
still holds an overwhelming stake.

323
00:20:11,710 --> 00:20:13,128
Nora once mentioned

324
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:15,839
that if she survived
the three-month probationary period,

325
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:18,884
Chairman Kang promised to reward her
with Kang Myeong-hwi's 9%.

326
00:20:18,967 --> 00:20:20,552
Yeah, that's right.

327
00:20:21,136 --> 00:20:23,513
He made that promise
after the funeral mass.

328
00:20:24,014 --> 00:20:26,433
Since Nora has survived
those three months,

329
00:20:26,516 --> 00:20:29,311
if she secures the promised 9% stake…

330
00:20:29,394 --> 00:20:30,938
KANG MYEONG-HWI, SON

331
00:20:32,356 --> 00:20:33,398
KANG PIL-BEOM

332
00:20:38,237 --> 00:20:39,571
KANG NORA, DAUGHTER

333
00:20:39,655 --> 00:20:43,575
If we add 14% to our preexisting 19,
we end up with 33%.

334
00:20:43,659 --> 00:20:45,661
This should be enough
to go up against Chairman Kang.

335
00:20:46,286 --> 00:20:48,997
Don't forget she came back
empty-handed from Switzerland.

336
00:20:49,081 --> 00:20:50,791
How are you so sure she'd be with us

337
00:20:50,874 --> 00:20:52,751
when she's about to be named
the successor?

338
00:20:52,834 --> 00:20:54,836
If we can't persuade her to join us,

339
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:56,713
we'll need to create a rift between them.

340
00:20:57,673 --> 00:21:01,218
Tomorrow, we'll launch
a public tender offer for Hanmin.

341
00:21:02,469 --> 00:21:03,595
A public tender offer?

342
00:21:03,679 --> 00:21:07,057
We offer a desirable price and scoop up
shares from small shareholders.

343
00:21:07,140 --> 00:21:08,892
From now on, we must do whatever it takes

344
00:21:08,976 --> 00:21:10,936
to acquire every share we can.

345
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:13,939
Okay.

346
00:21:22,948 --> 00:21:24,074
YEOUIDO PIRATES PLANS A SWEEP?
"WE'LL BUY THEM ALL AT HIGHER PRICES"

347
00:21:24,157 --> 00:21:25,117
AN ALL-OUT WAR WITH TENDER OFFER

348
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:27,452
HANMIN VS YEOUIDO PIRATES
SURGE IN STOCK PRICE FUELS MARKET CHAOS

349
00:21:27,536 --> 00:21:29,496
HANMIN VS YEOUIDO PIRATES
BATTLE IT OUT FOR MANAGEMENT CONTROL

350
00:21:29,579 --> 00:21:32,708
How in the world does
Hong Keum-bo think she can pull this off?

351
00:21:32,791 --> 00:21:35,002
-Two rolls each. That'll be 4,000 won.
-Okay.

352
00:21:35,085 --> 00:21:37,671
A purchase of two rolls
comes with complementary probiotics.

353
00:21:37,754 --> 00:21:39,089
-Thank you.
-Sure.

354
00:21:39,172 --> 00:21:41,133
Thank you so much.

355
00:21:43,844 --> 00:21:44,928
This is a piece of cake.

356
00:21:50,183 --> 00:21:51,518
It's time for an honest conversation.

357
00:21:53,270 --> 00:21:55,022
HANMIN VS YEOUIDO PIRATES
BATTLE IT OUT FOR MANAGEMENT CONTROL

358
00:21:55,105 --> 00:21:56,481
Ms. Hong is involved, right?

359
00:22:00,235 --> 00:22:01,445
I've always

360
00:22:01,528 --> 00:22:03,488
wanted to befriend her.

361
00:22:05,282 --> 00:22:06,533
And?

362
00:22:08,243 --> 00:22:09,786
So I placed my shares with her.

363
00:22:13,165 --> 00:22:15,167
Then do you know
the source of her funds as well?

364
00:22:19,796 --> 00:22:20,630
Big Al.

365
00:22:24,801 --> 00:22:25,761
Big Al?

366
00:22:29,890 --> 00:22:30,807
What's gotten into you?

367
00:22:34,811 --> 00:22:35,729
I can't tell you everything.

368
00:22:35,812 --> 00:22:36,813
Okay.

369
00:22:38,774 --> 00:22:39,816
Our Captain Hong

370
00:22:41,109 --> 00:22:42,360
has a magical ledger.

371
00:22:42,444 --> 00:22:43,278
<i>Yehppee!</i>

372
00:22:43,904 --> 00:22:45,739
That's our seed money.

373
00:22:45,822 --> 00:22:47,407
Yong-gi and I have joined her.

374
00:22:47,991 --> 00:22:48,992
A ledger?

375
00:22:49,076 --> 00:22:50,118
Don't tell me…

376
00:22:50,202 --> 00:22:53,038
You have a copy
of the slush fund ledger, don't you?

377
00:22:53,121 --> 00:22:54,372
Could you maybe think of this

378
00:22:55,707 --> 00:22:58,543
not as a gamble
but as a final investment in me?

379
00:22:59,127 --> 00:23:01,046
You mean Chairman Kang's
slush fund ledger?

380
00:23:01,797 --> 00:23:02,631
You know about it too?

381
00:23:09,221 --> 00:23:10,055
Damn it!

382
00:23:10,138 --> 00:23:12,057
I can't believe Ms. Hong.

383
00:23:14,726 --> 00:23:15,936
Don't do it.

384
00:23:16,019 --> 00:23:17,813
-You'd better pick up, Ms. Hong.
-Come on.

385
00:23:19,564 --> 00:23:22,150
She'd obviously screen her calls
in a situation this critical.

386
00:23:22,734 --> 00:23:23,944
Damn it.

387
00:23:25,946 --> 00:23:28,198
Mr. Bang, that was quite an overreaction.

388
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:31,743
Could it be…

389
00:23:33,745 --> 00:23:34,746
What?

390
00:23:36,706 --> 00:23:38,333
Are you upset about being left out?

391
00:23:38,416 --> 00:23:39,417
No.

392
00:23:40,544 --> 00:23:41,419
Damn it.

393
00:23:41,503 --> 00:23:42,754
You totally are.

394
00:23:42,838 --> 00:23:45,507
-Why would I be upset?
-You totally are…

395
00:23:45,590 --> 00:23:47,384
Why haven't you left yet?

396
00:23:47,467 --> 00:23:48,927
You're totally feeling left out.

397
00:23:49,010 --> 00:23:50,220
Why you… Go!

398
00:23:50,303 --> 00:23:52,180
He's 40 and upset about being left out!

399
00:23:52,264 --> 00:23:53,557
He's totally upset!

400
00:23:54,558 --> 00:23:55,392
Don't ever come back!

401
00:23:59,688 --> 00:24:00,522
Damn it.

402
00:24:02,649 --> 00:24:03,650
Get your <i>gimbap</i> here!

403
00:24:06,278 --> 00:24:07,445
They're 1,000 won each!

404
00:24:22,294 --> 00:24:23,295
The chairman

405
00:24:24,713 --> 00:24:27,382
gave the order
to withdraw the VIP's slush fund.

406
00:24:27,465 --> 00:24:29,384
<i>Are we sure we can touch that?</i>

407
00:24:29,467 --> 00:24:30,552
<i>Given who we're up against--</i>

408
00:24:30,635 --> 00:24:33,763
We still have a year
until the interest payments are paid out.

409
00:24:33,847 --> 00:24:36,141
We can dip into it at our discretion

410
00:24:36,850 --> 00:24:38,894
and just top it back up
by the end of the year.

411
00:24:54,576 --> 00:24:55,744
Oh, boy.

412
00:24:59,539 --> 00:25:01,374
-There's nothing?
-They're all empty.

413
00:25:03,001 --> 00:25:05,420
They've all been withdrawn
with zero balances.

414
00:25:07,172 --> 00:25:09,925
Those seals never left that safe.

415
00:25:10,008 --> 00:25:12,385
The bankbooks, copies of IDs,
and the authorization letters

416
00:25:12,469 --> 00:25:14,054
are all with me!

417
00:25:17,557 --> 00:25:18,892
Is it Hong Keum-bo's doing again?

418
00:25:19,893 --> 00:25:22,270
You must have checked who withdrew it!

419
00:25:23,355 --> 00:25:28,026
All the funds were transferred
to Yeouido Pirates' corporate account.

420
00:25:31,696 --> 00:25:33,490
Hey, I think it's time

421
00:25:33,573 --> 00:25:34,991
we just secure what's ours now.

422
00:25:36,493 --> 00:25:37,494
Come on.

423
00:25:37,577 --> 00:25:40,830
-It's still not too late.
-Don't be a moron.

424
00:25:41,748 --> 00:25:42,582
I did not

425
00:25:42,666 --> 00:25:44,668
devote myself to Hanmin

426
00:25:45,335 --> 00:25:49,130
for 30 damn years for some chump change!

427
00:25:55,011 --> 00:25:56,179
Now, the chairman

428
00:25:57,097 --> 00:25:59,766
couldn't get rid of me,
even if he wanted to.

429
00:26:00,475 --> 00:26:01,393
He has no one left.

430
00:26:27,252 --> 00:26:28,295
HANMIN INVESTMENT &amp; SECURITIES

431
00:26:28,378 --> 00:26:29,587
<i>What did you say?</i>

432
00:26:30,714 --> 00:26:32,007
My apologies, sir.

433
00:26:32,090 --> 00:26:34,259
It seems Hong Keum-bo's team
stole those funds,

434
00:26:34,342 --> 00:26:36,970
knowing we couldn't report it publicly.

435
00:26:37,053 --> 00:26:40,515
How could they have possibly
stolen the VIP's slush fund?

436
00:26:40,598 --> 00:26:44,102
You and I are the only ones
who know about its existence!

437
00:26:44,185 --> 00:26:45,687
I fear Executive Director Oh--

438
00:26:45,770 --> 00:26:46,896
Hey!

439
00:26:47,397 --> 00:26:49,649
He only ever delivered
the interest payments.

440
00:26:49,733 --> 00:26:50,692
It was managed

441
00:26:51,192 --> 00:26:53,820
by you, Song Ju-ran!

442
00:26:55,363 --> 00:27:00,285
You accused Oh Deok-gyu
of stealing the OW slush fund.

443
00:27:01,578 --> 00:27:04,414
But he said he was innocent!

444
00:27:05,081 --> 00:27:06,291
The way I see it,

445
00:27:06,374 --> 00:27:10,337
you framed Oh Deok-gyu back then
to hide the fact that it was stolen,

446
00:27:10,420 --> 00:27:14,215
and now you've
stupidly let it spiral into this!

447
00:27:14,299 --> 00:27:15,133
That's not true.

448
00:27:15,216 --> 00:27:16,718
Please believe me, sir.

449
00:27:17,552 --> 00:27:19,679
Last summer, during the slush fund probe,

450
00:27:19,763 --> 00:27:24,184
the late President Kang Myeong-hwi
made contact with Hong Keum-bo, didn't he?

451
00:27:24,267 --> 00:27:27,270
I fear he may have
handed something over to her back then.

452
00:27:30,023 --> 00:27:31,566
Goddamn it!

453
00:27:32,233 --> 00:27:35,111
Goddamn it all!

454
00:27:35,195 --> 00:27:38,281
We should first request
additional financing from DK Ventures

455
00:27:39,407 --> 00:27:41,117
to roll over the maturing bonds--

456
00:27:41,201 --> 00:27:42,410
Shut it!

457
00:27:43,078 --> 00:27:45,705
Are you seriously suggesting that
as an option right now?

458
00:27:46,748 --> 00:27:47,832
Are you telling me

459
00:27:47,916 --> 00:27:52,504
I should go beg for another handout
from that damn weasel?

460
00:27:58,093 --> 00:27:59,344
Unbelievable.

461
00:28:04,265 --> 00:28:07,143
We were only supposed to use Hanmin
as a basecamp.

462
00:28:07,685 --> 00:28:09,771
You once bought Hanmin bonds with me,

463
00:28:09,854 --> 00:28:12,690
but now you're snapping up stocks
at Yeouido Pirates?

464
00:28:13,274 --> 00:28:14,401
You're doing the complete opposite.

465
00:28:15,652 --> 00:28:16,778
With what money?

466
00:28:16,861 --> 00:28:18,154
We have enough funds.

467
00:28:18,238 --> 00:28:20,115
Your bonds will become worthless

468
00:28:20,198 --> 00:28:23,076
if Yeouido Pirates
becomes the controlling shareholder.

469
00:28:23,618 --> 00:28:25,078
So choose wisely,

470
00:28:25,578 --> 00:28:28,540
and remember that
Yeouido Pirates and I are key variables.

471
00:28:30,250 --> 00:28:33,920
Chairman Kang will reach out to you
to cover the bond maturity next week.

472
00:28:34,587 --> 00:28:35,713
If I were you,

473
00:28:35,797 --> 00:28:37,006
I would turn him down.

474
00:28:38,633 --> 00:28:41,261
But Chairman Kang will retaliate.

475
00:28:41,344 --> 00:28:44,389
So you'll pour money down the drain
because you're afraid?

476
00:28:45,265 --> 00:28:48,143
I'm giving you a chance to make your exit.

477
00:28:55,233 --> 00:28:56,151
Please eat.

478
00:29:00,530 --> 00:29:01,531
Eat.

479
00:29:06,619 --> 00:29:08,204
Chairman, I…

480
00:29:15,003 --> 00:29:15,920
Sir.

481
00:29:16,004 --> 00:29:19,132
The chairman just barely managed
to take his first bite.

482
00:29:19,215 --> 00:29:20,091
What could be so…

483
00:29:22,594 --> 00:29:26,306
DK Ventures faxed a notice of intent
to withdraw from the investment agreement.

484
00:29:26,389 --> 00:29:27,640
What did you say?

485
00:29:30,518 --> 00:29:32,270
INVESTMENT AGREEMENT WITHDRAWAL
AND BOND SALE NOTICE

486
00:29:32,353 --> 00:29:33,855
These bastards!

487
00:29:34,355 --> 00:29:36,316
-Get them on the phone!
-Yes, sir.

488
00:29:36,399 --> 00:29:37,859
I can't believe this.

489
00:29:47,243 --> 00:29:48,953
He's not picking up?

490
00:29:49,454 --> 00:29:50,455
Why this little…

491
00:29:57,629 --> 00:29:58,463
Nora.

492
00:29:58,546 --> 00:30:00,882
Is the company on shaky ground right now?

493
00:30:00,965 --> 00:30:01,800
How would I know?

494
00:30:03,760 --> 00:30:05,970
Get back in there
and at least pretend to be worried.

495
00:30:06,054 --> 00:30:07,222
Go on. Hurry.

496
00:30:07,305 --> 00:30:08,723
How could I when I know nothing?

497
00:30:08,807 --> 00:30:10,725
You just dragged me out.

498
00:30:12,268 --> 00:30:13,561
Seriously?

499
00:30:16,815 --> 00:30:19,776
DK Ventures has notified Hanmin
of the withdrawal of its investment,

500
00:30:19,859 --> 00:30:21,361
but our situation isn't ideal either.

501
00:30:22,612 --> 00:30:24,280
Stock prices jumped
because of the tender offers,

502
00:30:24,364 --> 00:30:26,825
and we're burning through our funds
to buy shares.

503
00:30:46,094 --> 00:30:47,262
They seemed really close.

504
00:30:47,846 --> 00:30:50,306
It appeared to be more than
a mere work-for-hire arrangement.

505
00:30:50,974 --> 00:30:52,392
You'll use this against her, right?

506
00:30:52,475 --> 00:30:54,227
We can't afford to hold back right now.

507
00:31:10,577 --> 00:31:13,997
The one-percent stake in Hanmin I received
from the divorce settlement?

508
00:31:14,956 --> 00:31:17,083
You want me to take your side with that?

509
00:31:21,212 --> 00:31:22,130
Why would I do that?

510
00:31:23,214 --> 00:31:24,757
We might not be husband and wife anymore,

511
00:31:24,841 --> 00:31:28,428
but he and I are still connected
through our Nora.

512
00:31:28,511 --> 00:31:30,930
So why would I betray the chairman?

513
00:31:38,813 --> 00:31:39,814
Nora.

514
00:31:40,815 --> 00:31:44,152
Do you recognize the man
sitting next to Ms. Song?

515
00:31:47,614 --> 00:31:48,865
What in the world is this?

516
00:31:48,948 --> 00:31:50,199
Ms. Song has a man she's seeing?

517
00:31:50,283 --> 00:31:53,161
The man who tried to abduct Kang Eun-joo
when she was ten…

518
00:31:54,871 --> 00:31:55,788
That's him, isn't it?

519
00:31:58,291 --> 00:32:00,043
My goodness. Hold on.

520
00:32:00,835 --> 00:32:02,879
Why would Ms. Song do that?

521
00:32:02,962 --> 00:32:04,172
How dare she go after our bloodline?

522
00:32:04,255 --> 00:32:07,884
Albert and I also suspect
that these two people instigated

523
00:32:07,967 --> 00:32:10,053
President Kang Myeong-hwi's accident.

524
00:32:11,137 --> 00:32:12,972
What? Myeong-hwi's accident?

525
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:16,684
Does that mean
Albert's accusation was true?

526
00:32:17,977 --> 00:32:19,604
Even if it's just for Nora's safety,

527
00:32:19,687 --> 00:32:21,606
we need you to take a stand.

528
00:32:45,171 --> 00:32:47,840
What do you think you're doing?

529
00:32:47,924 --> 00:32:49,175
When Nora was ten,

530
00:32:49,717 --> 00:32:53,304
we had intruders break into our home
and attempt to kidnap her.

531
00:32:53,388 --> 00:32:55,139
Even back then,

532
00:32:55,223 --> 00:32:57,225
the police suspected an insider job.

533
00:32:57,308 --> 00:32:58,685
And today,

534
00:32:58,768 --> 00:33:00,103
I finally found the accomplice.

535
00:33:00,728 --> 00:33:01,854
Chairman,

536
00:33:01,938 --> 00:33:04,315
this woman has been deceiving us
this whole time!

537
00:33:05,316 --> 00:33:07,694
Where did you get these photos from?

538
00:33:07,777 --> 00:33:09,862
You'll answer my question first.

539
00:33:09,946 --> 00:33:10,947
It was you, wasn't it?

540
00:33:12,281 --> 00:33:13,199
No.

541
00:33:14,242 --> 00:33:15,243
This is a misunderstanding.

542
00:33:15,952 --> 00:33:16,786
A misunderstanding?

543
00:33:16,869 --> 00:33:19,747
You were also behind
Myeong-hwi's accident, weren't you?

544
00:33:19,831 --> 00:33:20,665
Am I wrong about this too?

545
00:33:21,249 --> 00:33:22,125
Come on now.

546
00:33:22,208 --> 00:33:23,793
It's all in the past now--

547
00:33:23,876 --> 00:33:26,004
Why won't you believe me?

548
00:33:26,796 --> 00:33:30,717
Our Nora remembers
that kidnapper's face to this day.

549
00:33:31,634 --> 00:33:33,636
Are you certain?

550
00:33:34,887 --> 00:33:35,722
Yes.

551
00:33:36,347 --> 00:33:38,057
Ms. Song,

552
00:33:38,141 --> 00:33:40,184
why don't you explain
those pictures first?

553
00:33:45,273 --> 00:33:46,441
An old friend from my hometown

554
00:33:47,025 --> 00:33:49,485
kept calling
because he was strapped for cash.

555
00:33:49,569 --> 00:33:52,905
So I gave him a little something
and sent him on his way.

556
00:33:52,989 --> 00:33:54,949
I hadn't seen him in ten years.

557
00:33:55,450 --> 00:33:58,327
And as for that kidnapping incident,

558
00:33:58,911 --> 00:34:00,580
are you sure you're not mistaken,
Ms. Kang?

559
00:34:01,539 --> 00:34:02,957
It was so long ago,

560
00:34:03,041 --> 00:34:04,917
and you were just a child.

561
00:34:06,586 --> 00:34:07,462
Sir.

562
00:34:08,379 --> 00:34:12,258
I've never had a reason
to do something like that.

563
00:34:17,013 --> 00:34:18,181
If anything,

564
00:34:18,264 --> 00:34:23,352
I care about Ms. Kang
more than you ever have, ma'am.

565
00:34:23,436 --> 00:34:24,771
You're being

566
00:34:25,646 --> 00:34:26,731
far too emotional right now.

567
00:34:26,814 --> 00:34:28,900
-What? Emotional?
-Mom!

568
00:34:28,983 --> 00:34:30,777
Of course I'm emotional about my family.

569
00:34:30,860 --> 00:34:31,903
She's my daughter!

570
00:34:31,986 --> 00:34:35,406
Listen, we have bigger fires
to put out at the company.

571
00:34:35,490 --> 00:34:37,200
Let's talk about this later.

572
00:34:38,826 --> 00:34:40,119
I should've never

573
00:34:40,203 --> 00:34:42,371
come back to this damn house.

574
00:34:55,927 --> 00:34:57,762
He's just a friend
who runs errands for me.

575
00:34:58,596 --> 00:34:59,806
But I can swear to you

576
00:34:59,889 --> 00:35:02,809
I had no part in Ms. Kang's kidnapping.

577
00:35:04,018 --> 00:35:07,355
Let's focus on company matters for now.

578
00:35:10,191 --> 00:35:11,025
Yes, sir.

579
00:35:37,885 --> 00:35:39,011
Auntie,

580
00:35:39,512 --> 00:35:43,224
did you also move out with your mom then?

581
00:35:44,767 --> 00:35:46,936
I couldn't let her leave by herself.

582
00:35:47,854 --> 00:35:51,274
If I'm being honest,
I knew my father would do that.

583
00:35:59,949 --> 00:36:01,951
This is my favorite hairpin.

584
00:36:03,369 --> 00:36:06,289
This is a secret,
but wearing it gives you strength.

585
00:36:12,587 --> 00:36:13,754
Thanks.

586
00:36:24,557 --> 00:36:26,726
She's a celebrity.
We should get an autograph.

587
00:36:27,894 --> 00:36:28,853
She's our daughter's guest.

588
00:36:28,936 --> 00:36:30,479
Behave yourself, will you?

589
00:36:37,612 --> 00:36:38,905
We'll give you some privacy.

590
00:36:39,572 --> 00:36:41,115
Hello, I'm a big fan…

591
00:36:42,533 --> 00:36:44,076
I can't even get an autograph?

592
00:36:45,161 --> 00:36:46,495
Are you all right, ma'am?

593
00:36:48,581 --> 00:36:50,041
Of course not.

594
00:36:58,382 --> 00:37:02,136
I only came all this way

595
00:37:02,220 --> 00:37:05,973
because you came to me first
without going to the press.

596
00:37:07,058 --> 00:37:08,476
I figured I should at least thank you.

597
00:37:09,852 --> 00:37:12,480
Did you get a chance to speak to Ms. Song?

598
00:37:15,399 --> 00:37:16,442
She just denied it.

599
00:37:17,026 --> 00:37:19,320
But I know it was her doing.

600
00:37:19,904 --> 00:37:24,200
She was always dying to split up
the chairman and me.

601
00:37:24,951 --> 00:37:26,077
A misunderstanding?

602
00:37:26,160 --> 00:37:27,745
Misunderstanding, my ass.

603
00:37:28,371 --> 00:37:29,288
Damn wench.

604
00:37:40,091 --> 00:37:42,885
The one-percent stake I have in Hanmin…

605
00:37:44,011 --> 00:37:45,096
I'll give it to you.

606
00:37:45,972 --> 00:37:46,806
But

607
00:37:47,306 --> 00:37:48,307
keep Nora out of it.

608
00:37:49,684 --> 00:37:50,685
Pardon?

609
00:37:50,768 --> 00:37:52,937
Don't link my decision to hers.

610
00:37:53,020 --> 00:37:55,231
You're smart, so I assume you understand.

611
00:37:56,774 --> 00:37:58,651
Yes, I understand.

612
00:38:24,010 --> 00:38:25,886
Ms. Kang came into work today.

613
00:38:26,846 --> 00:38:27,972
Is that so?

614
00:38:28,055 --> 00:38:30,641
And I've confirmed
that an assistant who recently quit

615
00:38:30,725 --> 00:38:33,477
has joined Yeouido Pirates.

616
00:38:33,561 --> 00:38:34,603
And who might that be?

617
00:38:34,687 --> 00:38:37,064
It's Go Bok-hee,
Mr. Shin Jung-woo's former assistant.

618
00:38:37,898 --> 00:38:39,150
After some investigating,

619
00:38:39,233 --> 00:38:40,818
I've learned that she was accused

620
00:38:41,569 --> 00:38:42,987
of embezzlement at her previous jobs.

621
00:38:44,905 --> 00:38:46,657
So these punks were running

622
00:38:47,241 --> 00:38:50,494
a whole syndicate to steal the slush fund.

623
00:38:51,120 --> 00:38:54,749
I believe we can use their past histories
to question the origin of their funds

624
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:59,337
and arrange a small commotion for them.

625
00:39:02,590 --> 00:39:03,424
We must face them.

626
00:39:05,217 --> 00:39:07,595
Mr. Lee, you still work there,
so you're out.

627
00:39:09,764 --> 00:39:11,182
The three of us should go.

628
00:39:11,265 --> 00:39:12,933
What? Why are you excluding me?

629
00:39:13,017 --> 00:39:15,061
Ms. Song's out to get you.

630
00:39:15,144 --> 00:39:16,479
Who knows what trap awaits us?

631
00:39:16,562 --> 00:39:19,774
I'm sure she holds
a far deeper grudge against you.

632
00:39:19,857 --> 00:39:22,610
She even sent Go Bok-cheol
to my parents' restaurant.

633
00:39:22,693 --> 00:39:24,987
She also threatened you
with your embezzlement history.

634
00:39:26,155 --> 00:39:27,281
Exactly.

635
00:39:27,365 --> 00:39:30,409
I'm sick of running scared
and packing up when it's time.

636
00:39:32,912 --> 00:39:35,664
I'm done running away now.

637
00:40:04,485 --> 00:40:07,029
I'll hide the ashtray
as soon as we enter his office.

638
00:40:07,571 --> 00:40:08,864
My grandpa could throw it at us.

639
00:40:38,686 --> 00:40:40,729
You've had numerous meetings
with Chairman Kang.

640
00:40:40,813 --> 00:40:41,939
Has this ever happened?

641
00:40:42,022 --> 00:40:42,982
No.

642
00:40:43,065 --> 00:40:44,859
I don't see Ms. Song either.

643
00:40:53,701 --> 00:40:56,287
Go Bok-hee, you're under arrest
for embezzlement and theft.

644
00:40:56,370 --> 00:40:59,248
You have the right to remain silent
and the right to an attorney.

645
00:40:59,331 --> 00:41:00,416
What?

646
00:41:00,499 --> 00:41:02,376
We can talk more at the station.

647
00:41:02,460 --> 00:41:03,627
-Take her.
-Yes, sir.

648
00:41:03,711 --> 00:41:04,545
Wait.

649
00:41:05,129 --> 00:41:06,380
-My goodness.
-Let's go.

650
00:41:10,259 --> 00:41:11,177
Hold on.

651
00:41:12,178 --> 00:41:15,014
This isn't Ms. Go's workplace or her home.

652
00:41:15,097 --> 00:41:17,892
Who told you that she'd be here today?

653
00:41:18,976 --> 00:41:21,312
Please step aside.
We can't reveal our sources.

654
00:41:23,939 --> 00:41:25,399
-Let's go.
-Wait…

655
00:41:25,483 --> 00:41:27,276
Hold on a second. Wait!

656
00:41:28,402 --> 00:41:29,278
Hold on!

657
00:41:54,470 --> 00:41:56,514
I gave you several chances.

658
00:41:57,139 --> 00:41:58,682
Unfortunately, you're the weakest link.

659
00:42:01,268 --> 00:42:02,520
That's why you're the first to go.

660
00:42:08,067 --> 00:42:11,320
Then I guess you're next, Ms. Song?

661
00:42:12,446 --> 00:42:14,156
You're not much better off than me.

662
00:42:19,745 --> 00:42:22,331
<i>How do you manage to maintain</i>
<i>such a calm smile on your face</i>

663
00:42:22,414 --> 00:42:25,209
when the higher-ups
spew nonsense and dig into you?

664
00:42:29,421 --> 00:42:30,297
It's so I don't lose.

665
00:42:34,093 --> 00:42:36,804
You lose if you show tears
or falter in that moment.

666
00:42:38,222 --> 00:42:41,016
<i>I know how I really feel</i>
<i>behind that smile.</i>

667
00:42:48,732 --> 00:42:50,234
I'll go with her and get her a lawyer.

668
00:43:02,079 --> 00:43:03,122
Let's reschedule the meeting.

669
00:43:04,415 --> 00:43:05,833
Get back safely.

670
00:43:22,891 --> 00:43:25,686
ULLALA CHICKEN

671
00:43:25,769 --> 00:43:29,898
I was so shocked to see Ms. Go
walk out of the lobby in handcuffs.

672
00:43:31,400 --> 00:43:32,610
She'll be out in no time.

673
00:43:32,693 --> 00:43:34,528
Breaking into Ms. Song's safe?

674
00:43:34,612 --> 00:43:36,447
What could Ms. Song tell the police?

675
00:43:37,156 --> 00:43:40,451
The police weren't charging her
with anything related to Hanmin.

676
00:43:40,951 --> 00:43:44,204
Ms. Go was suspected of embezzlement
and theft by her former employers

677
00:43:44,288 --> 00:43:46,415
before she even joined Hanmin.

678
00:43:46,498 --> 00:43:47,708
Embezzlement?

679
00:43:47,791 --> 00:43:49,043
She can tell them it's not true.

680
00:43:49,126 --> 00:43:51,003
How can she when it's the truth?

681
00:43:51,086 --> 00:43:53,088
You of all people can't say that.

682
00:43:53,172 --> 00:43:55,049
Don't you remember what Queen Bee told us?

683
00:43:55,132 --> 00:43:57,134
She said she was never once caught.

684
00:43:57,217 --> 00:43:58,969
And she still wouldn't have been caught

685
00:43:59,053 --> 00:44:02,014
if she hadn't gotten involved with you
or this Yeouido Pirates business.

686
00:44:02,097 --> 00:44:03,432
So are you saying it's my fault?

687
00:44:03,515 --> 00:44:06,143
You say whatever you want
and order everyone around.

688
00:44:06,226 --> 00:44:07,394
Why can't I?

689
00:44:08,562 --> 00:44:09,730
Auntie, what's wrong with you?

690
00:44:09,813 --> 00:44:11,231
I'm not like Albert.

691
00:44:11,315 --> 00:44:13,317
I don't want to be arrested
like Queen Bee.

692
00:44:15,361 --> 00:44:18,113
Don't think I'll do as you say
just because everyone else does.

693
00:44:23,035 --> 00:44:23,869
Wait.

694
00:44:53,232 --> 00:44:54,066
Ju-ran.

695
00:44:55,150 --> 00:44:56,402
It appears the soft-hearted Nora

696
00:44:57,111 --> 00:44:59,530
has turned on Yeouido Pirates.

697
00:45:02,741 --> 00:45:05,369
PAST EMBEZZLEMENT ALLEGATIONS SURFACE
AGAINST KEY MEMBER OF YEOUIDO PIRATES

698
00:45:05,452 --> 00:45:08,163
FUNDING SOURCES OF YEOUIDO PIRATES'
VAST CAPITAL COME UNDER SCRUTINY

699
00:45:08,956 --> 00:45:09,998
THE BEAUTIFUL EMBEZZLER MS. GO'S SECRETS

700
00:45:10,082 --> 00:45:10,916
Ms. Go.

701
00:45:12,167 --> 00:45:14,545
They featured a nice picture of you.

702
00:45:16,255 --> 00:45:18,841
Anyway, you should be more worried
about Kang Nora than me.

703
00:45:18,924 --> 00:45:21,135
We're supposed to be
meeting her again today.

704
00:45:21,218 --> 00:45:23,137
Try to talk her into it, President Shin.

705
00:45:23,846 --> 00:45:24,888
And you stay out of it.

706
00:45:24,972 --> 00:45:26,807
You should worry about yourself.

707
00:45:27,975 --> 00:45:30,477
I don't want to lose anymore either.

708
00:45:32,271 --> 00:45:34,064
Speaking of, let me say one thing.

709
00:45:36,275 --> 00:45:37,109
I want…

710
00:45:41,989 --> 00:45:43,657
the most expensive lawyer in the country.

711
00:45:44,408 --> 00:45:46,076
You have some money left over.

712
00:45:46,160 --> 00:45:47,244
Help me avoid detention,

713
00:45:47,327 --> 00:45:49,413
so even if I'm locked up later,
it'll be a short stint.

714
00:45:49,496 --> 00:45:50,497
Okay?

715
00:45:51,123 --> 00:45:52,124
Okay.

716
00:46:05,053 --> 00:46:07,347
You ignored that call

717
00:46:07,431 --> 00:46:09,808
almost as if you knew who was calling.

718
00:46:10,392 --> 00:46:12,186
Ms. Hong Keum-bo asked to meet today,

719
00:46:12,269 --> 00:46:13,353
but I didn't go.

720
00:46:14,271 --> 00:46:15,689
I see.

721
00:46:15,772 --> 00:46:19,943
I had you work in the company

722
00:46:20,027 --> 00:46:22,738
and live in the dorms

723
00:46:22,821 --> 00:46:24,615
because I wanted you

724
00:46:24,698 --> 00:46:28,202
to experience an ordinary, modest life.

725
00:46:29,745 --> 00:46:32,414
But it seems three months in the dorm

726
00:46:32,998 --> 00:46:36,168
brought you quite close to your roommates.

727
00:46:36,835 --> 00:46:38,754
I heard you visited one of them

728
00:46:38,837 --> 00:46:41,423
when she was in the hospital
not too long ago,

729
00:46:41,507 --> 00:46:44,927
and even went to the restaurant
that Hong Keum-bo's parents run.

730
00:46:45,844 --> 00:46:48,680
I shared a room with the one
who was hospitalized.

731
00:46:49,473 --> 00:46:51,975
She's a single mother of a little girl.

732
00:46:52,059 --> 00:46:55,437
They reminded me
of my time with Mom in the US,

733
00:46:55,521 --> 00:46:56,939
so I wanted to take good care of them.

734
00:46:57,022 --> 00:46:58,565
I see.

735
00:46:59,566 --> 00:47:00,776
But you know,

736
00:47:00,859 --> 00:47:03,654
misguided sympathy is toxic.

737
00:47:04,279 --> 00:47:05,614
Those friends,

738
00:47:05,697 --> 00:47:06,990
your mother,

739
00:47:07,074 --> 00:47:08,992
and even your younger self.

740
00:47:10,118 --> 00:47:13,872
You need to let them all go
in order to grow.

741
00:47:15,207 --> 00:47:17,960
You need to put yourself first now.

742
00:47:19,545 --> 00:47:20,379
Then,

743
00:47:21,463 --> 00:47:23,006
I'd like you to keep your word as well.

744
00:47:24,132 --> 00:47:25,968
You said if I survived
the first three months here,

745
00:47:26,051 --> 00:47:28,053
I would get Myeong-hwi's shares.

746
00:47:29,972 --> 00:47:31,890
I'm going to put myself first now.

747
00:47:32,599 --> 00:47:33,600
Right.

748
00:47:33,684 --> 00:47:34,685
Sure.

749
00:47:40,732 --> 00:47:41,900
I've got breaking news.

750
00:47:42,901 --> 00:47:45,571
President Kang Nora now owns
9% more of the company.

751
00:47:45,654 --> 00:47:47,406
That brings her stake to 14%.

752
00:47:47,489 --> 00:47:48,824
How do you know about that?

753
00:47:48,907 --> 00:47:50,367
A shareholding disclosure was filed.

754
00:47:50,450 --> 00:47:51,952
Why were you looking at that?

755
00:47:52,035 --> 00:47:54,204
As a member
of Hanmin Investment &amp; Securities,

756
00:47:54,288 --> 00:47:56,915
at this critical time
when leadership is shifting…

757
00:47:58,041 --> 00:47:59,334
I can't just watch from the sidelines.

758
00:48:01,336 --> 00:48:05,048
I hear the chairman has been busy
parading her around after the transfer.

759
00:48:05,132 --> 00:48:07,926
It makes sense,
since he'd pay less in transfer taxes

760
00:48:08,010 --> 00:48:09,845
while the stock price is dismal.

761
00:48:09,928 --> 00:48:11,847
Why are you worrying
about rich people's taxes?

762
00:48:11,930 --> 00:48:13,265
I'm not worrying about the rich,

763
00:48:13,348 --> 00:48:16,059
I'm worrying about the company and myself.

764
00:48:16,143 --> 00:48:19,521
I should at least keep an eye
on where this company is headed.

765
00:48:22,357 --> 00:48:25,027
Mr. Lee Yong-gi,

766
00:48:25,110 --> 00:48:27,654
you couldn't even
look me in the eyes before.

767
00:48:30,115 --> 00:48:31,450
Look at that.

768
00:48:31,533 --> 00:48:33,577
Now, you talk back every chance you get.

769
00:48:33,660 --> 00:48:34,953
You've changed.

770
00:48:35,037 --> 00:48:36,371
I don't believe I've changed.

771
00:48:36,455 --> 00:48:38,040
I believe I've grown.

772
00:48:38,957 --> 00:48:39,791
If you'll excuse me.

773
00:48:43,003 --> 00:48:44,004
Unbelievable.

774
00:48:45,464 --> 00:48:46,423
Why is he perfectly fine?

775
00:48:47,049 --> 00:48:48,508
Humans are social creatures.

776
00:48:48,592 --> 00:48:49,843
Everyone has left.

777
00:48:50,636 --> 00:48:51,720
Why isn't he lonely?

778
00:48:54,264 --> 00:48:55,390
Why is this still so hot?

779
00:48:55,474 --> 00:48:57,976
The court has approved
Yeouido Pirates' request to convene

780
00:48:58,060 --> 00:48:59,978
an extraordinary shareholders' meeting.

781
00:49:01,563 --> 00:49:03,190
Unbelievable.

782
00:49:03,273 --> 00:49:04,858
What is the agenda item

783
00:49:04,941 --> 00:49:08,028
the Pirates want to raise
at the shareholders' meeting?

784
00:49:12,157 --> 00:49:13,367
It's the removal

785
00:49:14,117 --> 00:49:15,410
of Chairman Kang Pil-beom.

786
00:49:26,171 --> 00:49:27,464
Fine.

787
00:49:27,547 --> 00:49:29,049
Let's just keep our course.

788
00:49:30,217 --> 00:49:32,386
I, Kang Pil-beom,
am the controlling shareholder.

789
00:49:33,553 --> 00:49:37,140
Those bastards can't kick me out.

790
00:49:39,976 --> 00:49:41,186
Damn it.

791
00:49:42,354 --> 00:49:44,523
The date of the shareholders' meeting
has been set.

792
00:49:44,606 --> 00:49:46,942
It'll be February 23, 1998,
7 a.m. at the head office.

793
00:49:48,235 --> 00:49:49,111
At seven o'clock?

794
00:49:49,861 --> 00:49:51,446
That's awfully early.

795
00:49:51,530 --> 00:49:53,657
It's a petty trick
to deter shareholders from attending.

796
00:49:53,740 --> 00:49:57,119
Let's line up some shareholder disruptors
and control the mood at the meeting.

797
00:49:57,202 --> 00:49:58,286
Disruptors?

798
00:49:58,370 --> 00:50:00,622
They're paid plants
who get hired to steer the mood

799
00:50:00,706 --> 00:50:01,540
at shareholders' meetings.

800
00:50:02,124 --> 00:50:02,999
I see.

801
00:50:03,083 --> 00:50:04,126
So we're putting on a show?

802
00:50:04,209 --> 00:50:05,127
That's right.

803
00:50:05,210 --> 00:50:08,088
They'll try to stop us on the first floor,
so we'll split up to gain access.

804
00:50:08,171 --> 00:50:11,550
We'll send out press kits in bulk
and pack the meeting with reporters.

805
00:50:13,552 --> 00:50:15,721
Make sure to shut down any scenario

806
00:50:16,221 --> 00:50:18,181
that puts us
at a disadvantage in the vote.

807
00:50:18,265 --> 00:50:23,019
Start with strict ID checks
at the first-floor entrance,

808
00:50:23,103 --> 00:50:26,898
and pull in some able-bodied male staff
from the branches to stand guard.

809
00:50:27,607 --> 00:50:29,693
Our people should be the only ones

810
00:50:29,776 --> 00:50:32,279
inside the shareholders' meeting hall.

811
00:50:32,362 --> 00:50:34,448
-Yes, sir. Understood.
-Yes, sir. Understood.

812
00:50:36,074 --> 00:50:37,117
Good.

813
00:50:43,707 --> 00:50:44,708
Hey, Mi-sook.

814
00:50:44,791 --> 00:50:48,962
I heard the branch manager
and male employees talking earlier.

815
00:50:51,757 --> 00:50:53,800
Two staff members from Magang Branch alone

816
00:50:53,884 --> 00:50:55,552
have been recruited
for the shareholders' meeting.

817
00:50:56,052 --> 00:50:58,305
<i>Last time, they had young male employees</i>

818
00:50:58,388 --> 00:51:02,017
buy exactly one stock,
and then reimbursed them in cash.

819
00:51:02,726 --> 00:51:03,643
I see.

820
00:51:05,645 --> 00:51:08,148
Then some of the people fired
in the last restructuring

821
00:51:08,231 --> 00:51:10,776
must still own a Hanmin stock, right?

822
00:51:11,526 --> 00:51:12,611
Right.

823
00:51:12,694 --> 00:51:14,196
All right. Thanks.

824
00:51:16,114 --> 00:51:19,284
What if fired employees were mobilized
for past shareholders' meetings?

825
00:51:19,367 --> 00:51:21,912
They'd have a share of Hanmin stock

826
00:51:21,995 --> 00:51:23,872
and be eligible to attend the meeting.

827
00:51:28,877 --> 00:51:30,587
EMERGENCY CONTACT LIST

828
00:51:30,670 --> 00:51:33,381
I'm calling about
the Hanmin shareholders' meeting.

829
00:51:33,465 --> 00:51:35,383
-Is this Mr. Kim from Sales?
-Yes.

830
00:51:35,467 --> 00:51:36,885
That's correct.

831
00:51:36,968 --> 00:51:38,053
Do you still own a share?

832
00:51:38,136 --> 00:51:40,388
Thank you for joining. We'll see you then.

833
00:51:40,472 --> 00:51:41,598
You sold it?

834
00:51:41,681 --> 00:51:43,016
I understand. Thank you.

835
00:51:43,099 --> 00:51:44,976
TRADING DIVISION
GENERAL MANAGER, SO GYEONG-DONG

836
00:51:50,148 --> 00:51:53,443
GENERAL MANAGER, SO GYEONG-DONG

837
00:51:53,527 --> 00:51:56,029
RESIGNED

838
00:52:00,158 --> 00:52:02,577
EXTRAORDINARY SHAREHOLDERS' MEETING
FEBRUARY 23, 1998

839
00:52:03,995 --> 00:52:05,330
Come this way.

840
00:52:05,413 --> 00:52:06,456
Please wait.

841
00:52:07,707 --> 00:52:08,542
Please come through.

842
00:52:14,464 --> 00:52:15,590
What's that about?

843
00:52:16,883 --> 00:52:18,176
Do we go for the front door?

844
00:52:19,261 --> 00:52:20,804
-Or a side door?
-Both?

845
00:52:21,388 --> 00:52:24,057
I'll go for the back entrance,
so draw some attention at the front.

846
00:52:25,892 --> 00:52:27,435
-Let's go.
-All right.

847
00:52:35,777 --> 00:52:36,945
Let's go!

848
00:52:53,211 --> 00:52:54,880
I'm a Hanmin shareholder.

849
00:52:55,463 --> 00:52:56,423
I belong here!

850
00:52:57,007 --> 00:52:58,049
Are you kidding me?

851
00:52:58,550 --> 00:52:59,384
What's wrong with you?

852
00:53:00,802 --> 00:53:02,304
We'll need time to check the names.

853
00:53:02,387 --> 00:53:03,680
Please wait.

854
00:53:16,318 --> 00:53:20,196
EXTRAORDINARY SHAREHOLDERS' MEETING
HANMIN INVESTMENT &amp; SECURITIES

855
00:53:34,586 --> 00:53:35,837
You all showed up early.

856
00:53:38,256 --> 00:53:39,174
All right.

857
00:53:40,592 --> 00:53:42,093
You're all here so early.

858
00:53:42,844 --> 00:53:44,137
Yes, hello.

859
00:53:45,555 --> 00:53:46,473
Hello there.

860
00:54:05,325 --> 00:54:06,868
They're out front.

861
00:54:18,880 --> 00:54:20,632
The extraordinary shareholders' meeting

862
00:54:20,715 --> 00:54:23,593
will commence promptly at seven o'clock.

863
00:54:41,403 --> 00:54:42,237
Charge!

864
00:54:54,791 --> 00:54:56,418
<i>The meeting will be on the fifth floor,</i>

865
00:54:56,501 --> 00:54:58,044
<i>so I'll leave the emergency exit open.</i>

866
00:55:03,883 --> 00:55:05,093
This can't be.

867
00:55:09,973 --> 00:55:10,890
TEMPORARILY CLOSED

868
00:55:12,684 --> 00:55:13,893
Hello.

869
00:55:23,069 --> 00:55:23,903
Step aside.

870
00:55:30,368 --> 00:55:31,369
Ms. Hong.

871
00:55:34,039 --> 00:55:36,708
I've left the door up here open.

872
00:55:37,917 --> 00:55:40,920
Take the elevator and go down one floor.

873
00:55:42,547 --> 00:55:43,590
This is…

874
00:55:45,467 --> 00:55:46,426
all I can do for you.

875
00:55:53,391 --> 00:55:54,392
Let's go.

876
00:55:57,896 --> 00:55:59,022
Right this way, sir.

877
00:55:59,731 --> 00:56:01,274
Please make your way inside.

878
00:56:03,902 --> 00:56:04,903
Just a moment.

879
00:56:05,862 --> 00:56:09,282
Shareholders holding a single share
need to wait on the side.

880
00:56:09,365 --> 00:56:11,367
Are you discriminating
against small shareholders?

881
00:56:11,451 --> 00:56:13,328
One is enough to make me a shareholder!

882
00:56:19,584 --> 00:56:20,502
Give me a second.

883
00:56:22,378 --> 00:56:24,089
Hello, Mr. So.

884
00:56:32,180 --> 00:56:33,014
Hey!

885
00:56:34,474 --> 00:56:36,142
Don't you know Division Manager So?

886
00:56:36,226 --> 00:56:38,520
Show him and his men in.

887
00:56:38,603 --> 00:56:40,688
They're clearly branch employees.

888
00:56:41,189 --> 00:56:42,065
Yes, sir.

889
00:56:42,148 --> 00:56:42,982
This way, sir.

890
00:56:43,066 --> 00:56:44,776
<i>The time is now seven o'clock,</i>

891
00:56:44,859 --> 00:56:46,820
<i>so the shareholders' meeting</i>
<i>will commence.</i>

892
00:57:10,760 --> 00:57:13,096
EXTRAORDINARY SHAREHOLDERS' MEETING
FEBRUARY 23, 1998

893
00:57:25,900 --> 00:57:26,734
All right.

894
00:57:29,195 --> 00:57:33,408
The Pirates' disruptors were stopped
at the front and hall entrances,

895
00:57:33,491 --> 00:57:34,492
with Albert included.

896
00:57:35,493 --> 00:57:36,744
Is that so?

897
00:57:39,414 --> 00:57:41,791
The special item on today's agenda,

898
00:57:41,875 --> 00:57:44,252
submitted by Yeouido Pirates,
the second-largest shareholder,

899
00:57:44,335 --> 00:57:46,045
is a motion to dismiss Chairman Kang.

900
00:57:47,046 --> 00:57:48,006
For the motion to pass,

901
00:57:48,089 --> 00:57:52,135
at least one-third of the issued shares
with voting rights must be present,

902
00:57:52,218 --> 00:57:56,014
and at least two-thirds of the represented
must vote in favor.

903
00:57:56,639 --> 00:57:57,765
Before we proceed--

904
00:57:57,849 --> 00:57:59,684
I vote in favor
of dismissing Chairman Kang!

905
00:58:00,560 --> 00:58:02,729
-I vote in favor!
-Reinstate the laid-off workers!

906
00:58:02,812 --> 00:58:04,522
-Reinstate us!
-Reinstate us!

907
00:58:04,606 --> 00:58:06,691
Dismiss Chairman Kang Pil-beom!

908
00:58:06,774 --> 00:58:08,359
-Dismiss him!
-Dismiss him!

909
00:58:08,443 --> 00:58:10,320
Reinstate the laid-off workers!

910
00:58:10,403 --> 00:58:11,571
-Reinstate us!
-Reinstate us!

911
00:58:11,654 --> 00:58:13,907
Dismiss Chairman Kang Pil-beom!

912
00:58:13,990 --> 00:58:15,533
-Dismiss him!
-Dismiss him!

913
00:58:21,080 --> 00:58:22,874
You see,

914
00:58:23,666 --> 00:58:27,378
I spent 26 years and 11 months at Hanmin.

915
00:58:28,713 --> 00:58:30,965
I may not have always been at my best,

916
00:58:31,049 --> 00:58:34,093
but I thought I was making
the best choices I could.

917
00:58:35,929 --> 00:58:38,556
In hindsight,
I see that I made one too many

918
00:58:39,641 --> 00:58:41,226
cowardly and shameful choices.

919
00:58:43,394 --> 00:58:46,231
As for what really happened
with the order error incident,

920
00:58:46,731 --> 00:58:48,233
I assume you already know.

921
00:58:49,692 --> 00:58:50,568
It's much too late,

922
00:58:51,152 --> 00:58:52,153
but I'd like to apologize.

923
00:58:56,115 --> 00:58:58,243
After Chairman Kang is dismissed,

924
00:58:58,326 --> 00:59:01,287
we plan to reinstate
laid-off employees in phases.

925
00:59:01,913 --> 00:59:03,998
How would you like to join us, Mr. So?

926
00:59:05,458 --> 00:59:07,835
It could be the best choice you can make.

927
00:59:17,637 --> 00:59:19,013
The blame for failed management

928
00:59:19,097 --> 00:59:21,641
rests squarely with senior leadership
and the owners.

929
00:59:21,724 --> 00:59:23,351
-Scapegoating the employees
-That…

930
00:59:23,434 --> 00:59:25,019
and laying them off is reprehensible!

931
00:59:25,103 --> 00:59:26,646
Reinstate the laid-off workers!

932
00:59:26,729 --> 00:59:28,398
-Reinstate us!
-Reinstate us!

933
00:59:28,481 --> 00:59:30,316
Dismiss Chairman Kang Pil-beom!

934
00:59:30,400 --> 00:59:31,693
-Dismiss him!
-Dismiss him!

935
00:59:31,776 --> 00:59:33,695
Reinstate the laid-off workers!

936
00:59:33,778 --> 00:59:34,988
-Reinstate us!
-Reinstate us!

937
00:59:35,071 --> 00:59:37,156
Dismiss Chairman Kang Pil-beom!

938
00:59:37,240 --> 00:59:40,493
Any disruptive behavior in the hall
will result in removal from the venue.

939
00:59:40,577 --> 00:59:42,453
-Reinstate us!
-Reinstate us!

940
00:59:42,537 --> 00:59:44,497
Dismiss Chairman Kang Pil-beom!

941
01:00:06,477 --> 01:00:09,564
Let's start with the vote on the motion
to dismiss Chairman Kang Pil-beom.

942
01:00:16,654 --> 01:00:19,282
At today's shareholders' meeting,
Yeouido Pirates announces

943
01:00:19,365 --> 01:00:22,285
its support for the motion to dismiss
Hanmin's Chairman Kang Pil-beom.

944
01:00:22,368 --> 01:00:25,330
Out of a total of
90 million issued shares of Hanmin,

945
01:00:25,413 --> 01:00:28,207
Yeouido Pirates has secured
a total of 31 million shares,

946
01:00:28,291 --> 01:00:30,335
including shares represented by proxy,

947
01:00:30,418 --> 01:00:34,005
thereby obtaining the support of more
than one-third of the outstanding shares.

948
01:00:40,261 --> 01:00:42,889
We will now proceed to a ballot vote.

949
01:00:44,432 --> 01:00:46,100
Shareholders who support the motion,

950
01:00:46,184 --> 01:00:48,311
please mark your ballots and submit them.

951
01:01:10,375 --> 01:01:11,751
IN FAVOR

952
01:01:11,834 --> 01:01:12,877
IN FAVOR

953
01:01:31,354 --> 01:01:33,856
The percentage of voting rights present

954
01:01:34,857 --> 01:01:37,360
cast in favor of
Chairman Kang Pil-beom's removal

955
01:01:37,860 --> 01:01:39,904
was 41.4%,

956
01:01:39,987 --> 01:01:42,532
and failed to meet the threshold
for a special resolution.

957
01:01:44,325 --> 01:01:47,829
Therefore, I officially declare
this motion defeated.

958
01:01:57,797 --> 01:01:59,674
How dare they try me?

959
01:02:03,386 --> 01:02:05,054
Thank you for your hard work.

960
01:02:05,722 --> 01:02:06,931
Well done.

961
01:02:07,515 --> 01:02:09,350
Until next time.

962
01:02:14,063 --> 01:02:15,273
Thank you for today.

963
01:02:43,342 --> 01:02:45,052
They got So Gyeong-dong too?

964
01:02:45,928 --> 01:02:47,847
When did he join their side?

965
01:02:48,806 --> 01:02:51,100
They all used to wait with bated breath,

966
01:02:51,184 --> 01:02:55,062
anxiously hanging on my every word!

967
01:02:55,146 --> 01:02:57,356
You still won, Father.

968
01:03:01,235 --> 01:03:02,153
Ms. Song.

969
01:03:02,737 --> 01:03:05,198
Prepare for our first
press conference of the year.

970
01:03:06,282 --> 01:03:07,533
Now is the time

971
01:03:08,034 --> 01:03:12,705
to announce Nora to the world
as the new face of Hanmin.

972
01:03:20,338 --> 01:03:23,049
YEOUIDO PIRATES' FAILED TAKEOVER OF HANMIN
HAVE THEY BECOME A SINKING SHIP?

973
01:03:23,132 --> 01:03:25,551
KANG PIL-BEOM GOING STRONG
WHERE IS HANMIN HEADED NOW?

974
01:03:26,135 --> 01:03:28,387
AFTER SECURING MANAGEMENT CONTROL,
PRESIDENT KANG NORA TAKES LEAD

975
01:03:28,471 --> 01:03:30,431
"…and members of the press, I'm--"

976
01:03:30,515 --> 01:03:31,516
1998, DAY OF NEW YEAR CONFERENCE

977
01:03:31,599 --> 01:03:35,019
"I'm Kang Nora, the president of Hanmin."

978
01:03:35,102 --> 01:03:39,232
"In light of the unfortunate developments
surrounding Hanmin…"

979
01:03:39,315 --> 01:03:41,484
Have you memorized
the press statement I gave you?

980
01:03:42,443 --> 01:03:44,070
Yes, almost.

981
01:03:44,779 --> 01:03:45,905
About 61%?

982
01:03:50,284 --> 01:03:51,160
Option one.

983
01:03:51,744 --> 01:03:54,038
A clean-cut, classic suit.

984
01:03:54,121 --> 01:03:57,750
It aims to deliver a message
about continuing our tradition and legacy.

985
01:03:58,960 --> 01:03:59,794
Option two.

986
01:03:59,877 --> 01:04:02,713
It reflects a youthful,
future-oriented image

987
01:04:02,797 --> 01:04:06,717
aimed at increasing brand awareness
among the younger age demographic.

988
01:04:12,974 --> 01:04:13,850
Hello?

989
01:04:30,157 --> 01:04:31,158
Who was that?

990
01:04:32,285 --> 01:04:34,996
Only a few people know your Korean number.

991
01:04:36,581 --> 01:04:37,415
It was my mom.

992
01:04:37,498 --> 01:04:39,709
She said I should make sure
I'm presentable.

993
01:04:44,505 --> 01:04:45,673
Be careful around the chairman.

994
01:04:47,466 --> 01:04:49,802
I'll be here ten minutes early
to escort you.

995
01:04:55,224 --> 01:04:57,768
I recommend the first option.

996
01:04:58,853 --> 01:04:59,729
Okay.

997
01:05:36,974 --> 01:05:38,809
KANG EUN-JOO

998
01:05:43,773 --> 01:05:44,982
HANMIN INVESTMENT &amp; SECURITIES

999
01:05:48,110 --> 01:05:49,987
PRESIDENT KANG NORA'S
NEW YEAR PRESS CONFERENCE

1000
01:06:04,001 --> 01:06:05,044
What are you doing?

1001
01:06:06,754 --> 01:06:08,464
Oh, my outfit?

1002
01:06:09,173 --> 01:06:11,759
I know you prepared several options,

1003
01:06:11,842 --> 01:06:15,554
but is there a better outfit
to symbolize the past, present, and future

1004
01:06:16,514 --> 01:06:18,975
than our uniform?

1005
01:06:38,244 --> 01:06:41,497
Hello, I'm Kang Nora, the president
of Hanmin Investment &amp; Securities.

1006
01:06:41,580 --> 01:06:42,832
Before I became president,

1007
01:06:42,915 --> 01:06:47,211
I joined Hanmin on September 1, 1997,
as an entry-level employee,

1008
01:06:47,294 --> 01:06:50,381
under my childhood name of Kang Eun-joo.

1009
01:06:50,464 --> 01:06:54,468
Chairman Kang Pil-beom wished for me
to start at the bottom

1010
01:06:54,552 --> 01:06:57,471
and learn alongside ordinary people.

1011
01:06:57,555 --> 01:06:58,848
Well done, sir.

1012
01:07:06,605 --> 01:07:08,441
That's also when I left home

1013
01:07:08,524 --> 01:07:11,736
and moved into the Seoul City Dormitory
for Single Female Workers

1014
01:07:11,819 --> 01:07:13,738
to live with roommates for three months.

1015
01:07:16,198 --> 01:07:19,910
That was when I learned family is about
sharing meals, laughing together,

1016
01:07:19,994 --> 01:07:21,412
and even arguing at times.

1017
01:07:24,457 --> 01:07:28,586
I consider every Hanmin employee
a member of my family.

1018
01:07:31,881 --> 01:07:33,758
For the sake of Hanmin

1019
01:07:33,841 --> 01:07:36,177
and for the sake of the Hanmin family,

1020
01:07:36,761 --> 01:07:40,347
I will exercise my shareholder rights
in support of Yeouido Pirates.

1021
01:07:40,431 --> 01:07:42,308
What's this now?

1022
01:08:29,438 --> 01:08:31,273
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

1023
01:08:31,857 --> 01:08:33,567
<i>They won't just stand by and watch.</i>

1024
01:08:33,651 --> 01:08:36,779
If it's all gone to hell,
let's take what's ours while we can.

1025
01:08:36,862 --> 01:08:38,405
<i>This is an urgent directive</i>
<i>from the chairman.</i>

1026
01:08:38,489 --> 01:08:40,616
<i>How much cash do you have on hand?</i>

1027
01:08:40,699 --> 01:08:43,577
<i>If Ms. Song, who knows too much</i>
<i>about the slush fund, is gone…</i>

1028
01:08:43,661 --> 01:08:45,329
<i>He could avoid a guilty verdict?</i>

1029
01:08:45,412 --> 01:08:47,081
<i>Chairman Kang is doing that on purpose.</i>

1030
01:08:47,164 --> 01:08:48,040
<i>He knows I can't speak up.</i>

1031
01:08:48,124 --> 01:08:50,042
<i>Stop being so stubborn.</i>

1032
01:08:50,126 --> 01:08:51,961
The defense had
also requested this witness.

1033
01:08:52,044 --> 01:08:54,046
<i>He is already in attendance</i>
<i>in the courtroom.</i>

1034
01:08:54,547 --> 01:08:56,423
<i>Nora, come meet me right now.</i>

1035
01:08:56,507 --> 01:09:00,636
-What is it?
<i>-Now, none of you can make it out alive.</i>

1036
01:09:00,719 --> 01:09:03,514
<i>Thank you for all your hard work</i>
<i>over the years.</i>

1037
01:09:05,683 --> 01:09:10,688
Subtitle translation by: Justin S. Kim
